              "id": "les-clf-02-02",
              "title": "Amazon S3 — Simple Storage Service",
              "order": 2,
              "content": "Amazon S3 is AWS's object storage service — one of the original AWS services and possibly the most versatile. It's used for virtually everything: static website hosting, backups, data lakes, media storage, and more.\n\n**Core Concepts:**\n- **Bucket:** Container for objects. Must have a globally unique name. Tied to a specific Region.\n- **Object:** The file you store in S3. Can be up to 5 TB in size. Each object has a key (path), value (data), metadata, and version ID.\n- **Prefix:** Simulated folder path in an object's key (e.g., 'images/profile/user123.jpg')\n\n**S3 Storage Classes (Know These for the Exam):**\n| Storage Class | Use Case | Retrieval Time | Cost |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| S3 Standard | Frequently accessed data | Milliseconds | Highest |\n| S3 Intelligent-Tiering | Unknown access patterns | Milliseconds | Auto-optimized |\n| S3 Standard-IA | Infrequently accessed | Milliseconds | Lower storage |\n| S3 One Zone-IA | Non-critical, infrequent | Milliseconds | Lower (single AZ) |\n| S3 Glacier Instant | Archive, occasional access | Milliseconds | Low |\n| S3 Glacier Flexible | Archive, rarely accessed | Minutes to hours | Very Low |\n| S3 Glacier Deep Archive | Long-term archive | 12–48 hours | Lowest |\n\n**S3 Key Features:**\n- **Versioning:** Keep multiple versions of an object to protect against accidental deletion\n- **Lifecycle Policies:** Automatically transition objects between storage classes or delete them\n- **Replication:** Cross-Region Replication (CRR) or Same-Region Replication (SRR)\n- **S3 Transfer Acceleration:** Speeds up uploads using CloudFront edge locations\n- **Static Website Hosting:** Host entire static websites directly from S3\n\n**S3 Durability & Availability:**\n- S3 Standard: 99.999999999% (11 nines) durability — virtually indestructible\n- S3 Standard: 99.99% availability\n\n**Access Control:**\n- Bucket Policies (JSON): Grant/deny access to buckets and objects\n- ACLs (legacy): Object-level permissions\n- Block Public Access: Account-level setting to prevent accidental public exposure",
