              "content": "AWS networking services form the backbone of any secure cloud architecture. The exam tests your understanding of the major networking services and their purposes.\n\n**Amazon VPC (Virtual Private Cloud):**\nA VPC is your own private, isolated network within AWS. It's like having your own data center in the cloud.\n- **Subnets:** Divide your VPC into public (internet-accessible) and private (internal-only) segments\n- **Internet Gateway (IGW):** Allows resources in public subnets to communicate with the internet\n- **NAT Gateway:** Allows resources in private subnets to initiate outbound internet connections\n- **Security Groups:** Stateful firewall at the instance level (traffic allowed in is automatically allowed out)\n- **Network ACLs (NACLs):** Stateless firewall at the subnet level (you must configure both inbound AND outbound rules)\n- **VPC Peering:** Connect two VPCs to route traffic between them privately\n\n**Amazon CloudFront:**\nAWS's Content Delivery Network (CDN). Caches your content at 400+ Edge Locations worldwide to reduce latency for global users. Also protects against DDoS attacks via AWS Shield integration.\n\n**Amazon Route 53:**\nAWS's highly available DNS service. Features include:\n- Domain registration\n- DNS routing policies: Simple, Weighted, Latency-based, Failover, Geolocation\n- Health checks for automatic failover\n\n**AWS Direct Connect:**\nDedicated private network connection from your on-premises data center to AWS. More reliable and consistent than internet-based connections.\n\n**AWS VPN:**\n- **Site-to-Site VPN:** Encrypted connection between on-premises network and AWS VPC\n- **Client VPN:** Allow individual users to connect to AWS securely",
