              "id": "les-clf-02-05",
              "title": "AWS Compute Beyond EC2",
              "order": 5,
              "content": "While EC2 is the most well-known compute service, AWS offers several other compute services that reduce operational overhead and can be more cost-effective for specific workloads.\n\n**AWS Lambda:**\nServerless compute. You upload your code, and AWS runs it in response to events — no servers to manage. Key characteristics:\n- Pay only for actual compute time (charged per millisecond)\n- Automatically scales\n- Supports Python, Node.js, Java, Go, Ruby, .NET, and custom runtimes\n- Maximum execution time: 15 minutes\n- Triggered by events: API Gateway, S3, DynamoDB streams, CloudWatch, etc.\n\n**AWS Elastic Beanstalk:**\nPlatform as a Service (PaaS). You upload your application code, and Elastic Beanstalk automatically handles capacity provisioning, load balancing, auto-scaling, and monitoring. You still control the underlying resources but don't need to manage them manually.\n\n**Amazon ECS (Elastic Container Service):**\nRun Docker containers at scale. Supports two launch types:\n- **EC2 launch type:** You manage the underlying EC2 instances\n- **Fargate launch type:** Serverless containers — no EC2 management\n\n**Amazon EKS (Elastic Kubernetes Service):**\nManaged Kubernetes. Run Kubernetes clusters without managing the control plane.\n\n**AWS Fargate:**\nServerless compute engine for containers. Works with both ECS and EKS. No server management required.\n\n**Comparison:**\n| Service | Abstraction Level | You Manage |\n|---|---|---|\n| EC2 | Low | OS, runtime, app |\n| Elastic Beanstalk | Medium | App code only |\n| ECS/EKS + EC2 | Medium | EC2 instances |\n| ECS/EKS + Fargate | High | App/container code |\n| Lambda | Highest | Function code only |",
